---
description: Agent working style for this repo
alwaysApply: true
---

Before making major changes:
1. inspect existing implementation
2. summarize current state
3. propose plan
4. then implement

When working:
- prefer small, reviewable changes
- explain tradeoffs clearly
- do not rewrite unrelated files
- preserve working production behavior unless explicitly improving it
- call out technical debt and schema mismatches

Protected files — never touch unless the task explicitly names them:
- `pages/_document.tsx` — global HTML shell; removing <Head /> breaks CSS for the entire app
- `pages/_app.tsx` — global app wrapper; changes affect every route, not just the page in scope
- `lib/supabase.ts` — DB client and shared types; schema changes belong in migrations
- `tailwind.config.js` — design token source of truth; do not add one-off values
- Any file in `migrations/` — never edit a migration once it has been written